<li id="cite_note-25"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/OpenBSD" title="OpenBSD">OpenBSD</a>'s <a href="/wiki/PF_(firewall)" title="PF (firewall)">pf</a> is a packet filter some providers use for exactly this purpose. <a href="https://gold.rayservers.com/ddos-protection" class="external autonumber" title="https://gold.rayservers.com/ddos-protection" rel="nofollow">[1]</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://mehmet.suzen.googlepages.com/qos_ios_dos_suzen2005.pdf" class="external text" title="http://mehmet.suzen.googlepages.com/qos_ios_dos_suzen2005.pdf" rel="nofollow">"Some IoS tips for Internet Service (Providers)"</a> (Mehmet Suzen)</li>
<li id="cite_note-27"><b><a href="#cite_ref-27" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://news.cnet.com/U.K.-outlaws-denial-of-service-attacks/2100-7348_3-6134472.html" class="external text" title="http://news.cnet.com/U.K.-outlaws-denial-of-service-attacks/2100-7348_3-6134472.html" rel="nofollow">Cnet</a></li>
</ol>
</div>
